description: Retrieves the current traffic distribution for a given traffic distribution group.

parameters.name: Id
parameters.description: The identifier of the traffic distribution group. This can be the ID or the ARN if the API is being called in the Region where the traffic distribution group was created. The ARN must be provided if the call is from the replicated Region.

nested_items.name: TelephonyConfig
nested_items.description: The distribution of traffic between the instance and its replicas.

nested_items.name: Region
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region where the traffic is distributed.

nested_items.name: Percentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of the traffic that is distributed, in increments of 10.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The identifier of the traffic distribution group. This can be the ID or the ARN if the API is being called in the Region where the traffic distribution group was created. The ARN must be provided if the call is from the replicated Region.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the traffic distribution group.

nested_items.name: SignInConfig
nested_items.description: The distribution that determines which Amazon Web Services Regions should be used to sign in agents in to both the instance and its replica(s).

nested_items.name: Region
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region of the sign in distribution.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: Whether sign in distribution is enabled.

nested_items.name: AgentConfig
nested_items.description: The distribution of agents between the instance and its replica(s).

nested_items.name: Region
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region where the traffic is distributed.

nested_items.name: Percentage
